<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb9711225-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3" identifier="/us/usc/t39/s3664"><num value="3664">§ 3664.</num><heading> Enforcement of orders</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The several district courts have jurisdiction specifically to enforce, and to enjoin and restrain the Postal Service from violating, any order issued by the Postal Regulatory Commission.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb9711226-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/109/435/tII/s205">Pub. L. 109–435, title II, § 205</ref>, <date date="2006-12-20">Dec. 20, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/3217">120 Stat. 3217</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
